
[1]sharp-sighted

   SH'ARP-SIGHTED, a. [sharp and sight.]

   1. Having quick or acute sight; as a sharp-sighted eagle or hawk.

   2. Having quick discernment or acute understanding; as a sharp-sighted
   opponent; sharp-sighted judgement.
